More Info: 

Requiem (2006) is a German language film by Hans-Christian Schmid starring Sandra Huller. The film has been promoted as a more truthful depiction of the real-life events of the exorcism of Anneliese Michel (September 21, 1952 - July 1, 1976), a German woman who was believed to have been possessed by six or more demons. These events also served as the the basis of Scott Derrickson&#039;s 2005 movie The Exorcism of Emily Rose.
